@Rob--W I'd like to work on this.
Added a SITE_URL to `.circleci/config.yml`
I'm new here, so can someone please let me know if my commit was correct?

Fixed a bug that resets the theme to a default theme when a shared theme link is loaded.

For the code here:
https://github.com/mozilla/FirefoxColor/blob/a43d5c66c7dc6f644f4e42e6a53ed1df9e19f099/src/web/index.js#L153-L157

First, I followed your suggestion and after a few changes I added an if condition:
Now the same lines look like:
```
if (!params.theme) {
  const state = store.getState();
  postMessage("addImages", {
    images: selectors.themeCustomImages(state)
  });
  postMessage("setTheme", { theme: selectors.theme(state) });
}
```
Since the bug occurs only when a shared link is opened, I decided to add a flag and check if the current page was a shared link or not using `params.theme` to check for ?theme, and it works!
if the page IS a shared link, then I added another `postMessage("fetchTheme");` here at line 281, the first line in the else block:
https://github.com/mozilla/FirefoxColor/blob/a43d5c66c7dc6f644f4e42e6a53ed1df9e19f099/src/web/index.js#L280-L290

I did that because, if the theme was not a shared link, the existing code already did a fetchTheme and worked properly. But if `params.theme` exists, there was no fetchTheme call.

Thanks!

